Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium light red-brown; mainly red inclusions. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Timokles. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX TAL 069. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 116, 14.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0573)
